WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
[Unknown]: I.V.M.

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
[Amit Varma]: I often say that the greatest mechanism of social service,

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:10.000
[Amit Varma]: of improving the lives of other people,

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:12.000
[Amit Varma]: is free markets.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:14.000
[Amit Varma]: Think about what happens in a market.

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:15.000
[Amit Varma]: Now everyone has needs.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:18.000
[Amit Varma]: Those needs can be fulfilled by others,

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:21.000
[Amit Varma]: either out of benevolence or out of self-interest.

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:23.000
[Amit Varma]: Now benevolence cannot be relied upon,

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:25.000
[Amit Varma]: but self-interest always can.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:27.000
[Amit Varma]: Let's say you are a greedy person.

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:29.000
[Amit Varma]: You're a sociopath who doesn't care about other people.

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:32.000
[Amit Varma]: In a free market, the only way you can make money

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:34.000
[Amit Varma]: and fulfill your own needs

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:36.000
[Amit Varma]: is by fulfilling someone else's need,

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:38.000
[Amit Varma]: by making them better off.

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:40.000
[Amit Varma]: Remember, every transaction in a free market

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:41.000
[Amit Varma]: is a positive sum game.

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:43.000
[Amit Varma]: Both people who transact are better off

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:45.000
[Amit Varma]: or they would not transact in the first place.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:48.000
[Amit Varma]: So the only way you can make money for yourself

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:50.000
[Amit Varma]: is by adding value to somebody's life.

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:52.000
[Amit Varma]: Markets are the mechanism

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:54.000
[Amit Varma]: that enable people to help themselves

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:56.000
[Amit Varma]: by helping others first.

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:59.000
[Amit Varma]: The beauty and elegance of this is quite mind-blowing.

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:01.000
[Amit Varma]: And it also stands to reason, therefore,

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:04.000
[Amit Varma]: that the more someone messes with this mechanism,

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:06.000
[Amit Varma]: the more someone gets in the way,

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:09.000
[Amit Varma]: the more harm they cause to society.

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:12.000
[Amit Varma]: Remember, the crux of markets, the reason they exist,

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:15.000
[Amit Varma]: is a value that someone is trying to add

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:17.000
[Amit Varma]: to the life of another human being.

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:20.000
[Amit Varma]: Nothing should be allowed to get in the way of that.

